{"id": "duc04-testb-13:3#9", "contents": "Thailand showcased its nearly complete facilities for the Asian Games to a delegation of heads of organizing committees from 43 competing nations on Thursday. The tour aimed to reassure the delegates, who had expressed concerns over the country's preparations for the event. Thailand had won the host rights in 1995, but faced setbacks that led the Olympic Council of Asia to threaten to move the games to another country late last year. However, it appeared that the tour was successful in alleviating doubts, with Abdul Muttaleb al-Ahmad, director general of the Olympic Council of Asia, stating that \"everything is 99 percent completed.\""}
